# Intuition and Approach

    1. Find left node indcated by index - l
    2. Find right node indicated by index - r
    3. Revers left node till right node
    4. Link the broken links

    Note: Add a dummy head to track left_prev node in case left node is at head

#### Please bear with my diagrams :)

Input: head = ```[1,2,3,4,5]```, l = ```2``` (left index), r = ```4``` (right index)
Output: ```[1,4,3,2,5]```

![20230907_111845_1.jpg](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/e5b2b627-ed02-4dca-a99e-751701ca1170_1694068233.7766912.jpeg)


# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(2r - l))$$ ```r```= right index, ```l``` = left index
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
# C++
```cpp
/**
 * Definition for singly-linked list.
 * struct ListNode {
 *     int val;
 *     ListNode *next;
 *     ListNode() : val(0), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x) : val(x), next(nullptr) {}
 *     ListNode(int x, ListNode *next) : val(x), next(next) {}
 * };
 */

class Solution {
public:
    ListNode* reverseBetween(ListNode* head, int l, int r) {
        // Dummy head insertion
        ListNode* dummy_head = new ListNode(-1);
        dummy_head->next = head;

        // 1st while loop (spot left_prev, left nodes)
        ListNode* left_prev = dummy_head;
        ListNode* left = dummy_head->next;
        int left_count = 1;  // we start with 1 because we have to stop previous to left (because dummy head added)
        while (left_count < l) {
            left_prev = left;
            left = left->next;
            left_count++;
        }
        // 2nd while loop (spot the right, right_next nodes)
        ListNode* right = left;
        ListNode* right_next = left->next;
        int right_count = 0;
        while (right_count < r - l) {
            right = right_next;
            right_next = right_next->next;
            right_count++;
        }
        // 3rd while loop (reverse element between left and right node)
        ListNode* cur = left;
        ListNode* pre = nullptr;
        while (cur != right_next) {
            ListNode* tmp = cur->next;
            cur->next = pre;
            pre = cur;
            cur = tmp;
        }
        // 4th fix breakage link
        left_prev->next = right;
        left->next = right_next;

        head = dummy_head->next;
        delete dummy_head;
        return head;
    }
};
```
