If we get the linked list from left to right separete from remaninig list we can easily reverse it.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Simply split the linked list int three parts 0<-->left-1 && left<-->right  && right+1<-->end .
To do this make some pointers as
(temp) ptr to traverse linked list.
(temp1) ptr to point to the node just before left one node.
(temp2) ptr to point to the node just before right one node.
(newh) this point to left one node(temp1->next) and used for reverse that list as head of linked list.
(end) to point on the node just after right one node used to reconnent them all.


Now, separate them in 3 parts by making temp1->next=NULL  and temp2->next->next=ULL and reverse the linked list with head as newh.

In the end join them again by making temp1->next=newh  and 
(last node of reversed list)->next=end.

