My intuition was that take each space as a record separator, so I can have the variable `$0` with the word. 

Then, with the word in `$0`, I can do the old trick of update an `awk` associative array and incrementing acording the appareances.

# Code
```
awk -v RS='[[:space:]]+' '{arr[$0]++}END{
    for(letra in arr)
        printf "%s %s\n", letra, arr[letra]
}' words.txt | sort -k2nr
```

